<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3689296>
    dc:description "FIG. 1. Calathus (Certocalathus) advena (LeConte, 1848), habitus, dorsal view; male specimen from Alaska: Afognak Is." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3689296/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3689298>
    dc:description "FIGS 2–4. Calathus (Certocalathus) advena (LeConte, 1848). Fig. 2: female genital tract, ventral view; Fig. 3: gonocoxites, ventral view; Fig. 4: aedeagus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: bc: bursa copulatrix; co: common oviduct; ds: dorsal ensiform seta; es: external ensiform setae; gc 1: basal gonocoxite; gc 2: apical gonocoxite; sp: spermatheca; sp-gl: spermathecal gland; spit: sensory pit; pm-l: left aedeagal paramere; pm-r: left paramere; vg: vagina." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3689298/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

